# API Endpoints

## GET

Retrieve all books

```
GET /books
```

Purpose:

Returns all book records.

Example Response

```json
[
    {
        "id":1,
        "title":"Python Programming",
        "author":"John Smith",
        "price":550
    }
]
```

---

## POST

Add new book

```
POST /books
```

Example Body

```json
{
    "title":"Learning SQL",
    "author":"Alan Beaulieu",
    "price":799.99,
    "category":"Database",
    "author_id":3
}
```

Purpose

Creates a new book record.

---

## PUT

Update existing book

```
PUT /books/4
```

Example

```json
{
    "title":"Advanced SQL",
    "price":999
}
```

Purpose

Updates an existing book.

---

## DELETE

Delete book

```
DELETE /books/4
```

Purpose

Removes book from database.

